# Context is the repo root; the content-hash stage digests this filtered tree to decide when a deploy
# fires. Exclude the huge/regenerable/irrelevant -- .git most of all (it churns every commit; hashing
# it would defeat "redeploy only on meaningful change"). node_modules is machine-specific too.
node_modules
**/node_modules
.git
.astro
.worktrees
.idea
dist
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
